ish laboratory of diversities”. In order to go through these steps, the author analyses three case studies, coming from the political/social agenda: education, workplace, and political rights. At the end, the reader will have an empirically informed and theoretically founded overview on how Spain is managing diversity. This book is timely for a wide range of academic and professional readers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCultural pluralismzSpainvCase studies. 0aCultural pluralismzSpain. 0aMulticulturalismzSpainvCase studies. 0aMulticulturalismzSpain. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aBarcelona.  aCity Councils.  aDanish cartoon affair.  aFII.  aMadrid.  aSpanish diversity.  aanti-discrimination policies.  adiversity management.  aeducation system.  aimmigrant associations.  ainstitutional change.  alabour market.  amosque debate.  apolicy innovation.  apolitical participation.  apractical philosophy.  avoting rights.1 aZapata-Barrero, Ricard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152610280540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526102805423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526102805/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles